column5: My son and I are thinking about heading to Minaki this week for some walleye and bass fishing. I have heard that this time of year the walleyes may be very deep(35 to 50 fow). We don't like to fish that deep since we like to C & R most fish. Any recent reports on activity, depths, water temp. would be great. Thanks, Jim
We are heading up Tuesday but won't be walleye fishing. Most of what we hear each year (been 20 years continuous for us in mid-September) is 24-27 ft.
